The next Biennial should be held at the Venetian in 2021 and the Venice Architecture Biennale in 2022.


More than 1,700 artists and academics have signed an open letter declaring that they will not participate in the upcoming edition of the Venice Architecture Biennale, which will take place in the Italian city from May 22 to May 28.“We recognize that this is a critical moment for the future of our cultural and artistic ecosystem,” reads the letter, which was written by art historians, architects, conservators, and other cultural figures, and was dated May 31. “We demand that the organizers of the exhibition take the following steps: ‘Act in a way that does not allow the cancellation of the exhibition or reduce its program in any way;

Implement a compensation plan that provides for the artists and institutions involved in the exhibition, including for the losses of income from the attendance of the public and the exhibition’s commercial and institutional sponsors, with an emergency funding plan for the artists’ immediate needs;

Implement a formal apology and compensation plan for the organizers; and

